#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:91
msgid ""
"The kernel or a userspace policy daemon can use these capabilities to modify "
"task placement decisions. For instance, if either the performance or energy "
"capabilities of a given logical processor becomes zero, it is an indication "
"that the hardware recommends to the operating system to not schedule any "
"tasks on that processor for performance or energy efficiency reasons, "
"respectively."
