#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:98
msgid "Implementation details for Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:100
msgid ""
"The implementation of threads scheduling consists of the following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:102
msgid ""
"A thread is spawned and scheduled to the ideal core using the default "
"heterogeneous scheduling policy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:104
msgid ""
"The processor profiles thread execution and assigns an enumerated "
"classification ID. This classification is communicated to the OS via logical "
"processor scope MSR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:108
msgid ""
"During the thread context switch out the operating system consumes the "
"workload (WL) classification which resides in a logical processor scope MSR."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:110
msgid ""
"The OS triggers the hardware to clear its history by writing to an MSR, "
"after consuming the WL classification and before switching in the new thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/x86/amd-hfi.rst:112
msgid ""
"If due to the classification, ranking table, and processor availability, the "
"thread is not on its ideal processor, the OS will then consider scheduling "
"the thread on its ideal processor (if available)."
msgstr ""

